brief_summary: To determine whether warfarin or lovastatin alone or in combination retarded the progression of atherosclerotic plaques in the carotid arteries of high risk individuals with asymptomatic carotid stenosis. Also, to determine if a full scale trial was feasible.
condition: Cardiovascular Diseases Carotid Stenosis Cerebral Arteriosclerosis Cerebrovascular Disorders Heart Diseases Vascular Diseases
eligibility_criteria: Men and women with early carotid atherosclerosis and moderately elevated LDL cholesterol between the 60th and 90th percentiles.
